This paper discusses privacy concerns in online social networks, specifically Facebook, and proposes a solution to improve privacy controls. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The study also considers the impact of a user interface on privacy controls, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper analyzes the composition of visible content, which could be categorized under cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the study examines the impact of country of origin on privacy, which could be classified under social computing (cs.SOC).
